THE MAN HAS GOTTEN BACK ON HIS

00:02:01.710 --> 00:02:03.881
FEET.

00:02:07.421 --> 00:02:08.758
&gt;&gt; Cytomander: SO EVEN THE

00:02:08.758 --> 00:02:09.660
GREAT GUAME, THE IMMOVABLE,

00:02:09.660 --> 00:02:11.429
WITH HIS DISTINGUISHED SERVICE,

00:02:11.429 --> 00:02:12.599
WAS GIVEN THE RUNAROUND

00:02:12.599 --> 00:02:14.101
BY HUMANS.

00:02:14.101 --> 00:02:15.137
PATHETIC.

00:02:15.137 --> 00:02:16.139
&gt;&gt; Guame: HUNH! I DON’T HAVE TO

00:02:16.139 --> 00:02:17.141
TAKE THAT FROM SOMEONE WHO

00:02:17.141 --> 00:02:18.143
NEVER LEAVES THE COMFORT OF THE

00:02:18.143 --> 00:02:20.113
CAPITAL.

00:02:20.113 --> 00:02:21.517
&gt;&gt; Cytomander: THE SPIRAL KING

00:02:21.517 --> 00:02:23.286
HAS BUT TO GIVE THE WORD, AND

00:02:23.286 --> 00:02:25.692
I, CYTOMANDER, WILL SET OUT.

00:02:25.692 --> 00:02:28.196
&gt;&gt; Lordgenome: AND ADIANE?

00:02:28.196 --> 00:02:30.200
&gt;&gt; SHE HAS YET TO RETURN.

00:02:30.200 --> 00:02:31.537
&gt;&gt; Cytomander: THAT WOMAN

00:02:31.537 --> 00:02:33.273
DOESN’T KNOW WHEN TO GIVE UP.

00:02:33.273 --> 00:02:35.243
&gt;&gt; Lordgenome: AND DAI‐GUNZAN?

00:02:35.243 --> 00:02:37.414
&gt;&gt; PROCEEDING ON A DIRECT COURSE

00:02:37.414 --> 00:02:38.450
HERE TO TEPPELIN.

00:02:38.450 --> 00:02:41.422
&gt;&gt; Lordgenome: WELL...

00:02:41.422 --> 00:02:43.426
&gt;&gt; Guame: IT WOULD SEEM FORTUNE

00:02:43.426 --> 00:02:45.464
IS TURNING IN ADIANE’S FAVOR.

00:02:45.464 --> 00:02:46.299
&gt;&gt; Cytomander: WHAT DO YOU MEAN

00:02:46.299 --> 00:02:46.767
BY THAT?

00:02:46.767 --> 00:02:47.502
&gt;&gt; Guame: THEY’RE HEADING

00:02:47.502 --> 00:02:49.539
STRAIGHT FOR THE SEA.

00:02:54.883 --> 00:02:58.156
&gt;&gt; Gimmy: WHAAH!

00:02:58.156 --> 00:02:59.693
LOOK AT THAT!

00:02:59.693 --> 00:03:02.431
IT’S A BIG WATER PUDDLE!

00:03:02.431 --> 00:03:03.701
&gt;&gt; Kittan: WHAT, ARE YOU GUYS

00:03:03.701 --> 00:03:04.936
STUPID OR SOMETHING?

00:03:04.936 --> 00:03:06.439
THIS "BIG PUDDLE" HERE IS

00:03:06.439 --> 00:03:07.509
WHAT WE CALL "THE SEA"!

00:03:07.509 --> 00:03:08.611
&gt;&gt; Gimmy: THE SEA?

00:03:08.611 --> 00:03:09.513
&gt;&gt; Kittan: IT’S WHERE WATER

00:03:09.513 --> 00:03:10.882
FROM RAIN AND RIVERS AND STUFF

00:03:10.882 --> 00:03:11.717
GATHERS FROM ALL AROUND THE

00:03:11.717 --> 00:03:12.585
WORLD.

00:03:12.585 --> 00:03:13.253
&gt;&gt; Gimmy: [gasps]

00:03:13.253 --> 00:03:14.221
&gt;&gt; Artenborough: YOU KNOW

00:03:14.221 --> 00:03:14.790
EVERYTHING.

00:03:14.790 --> 00:03:15.625
&gt;&gt; Nia: I’VE HEARD STORIES

00:03:15.625 --> 00:03:16.660
ABOUT IT BEFORE, BUT THIS IS MY

00:03:16.660 --> 00:03:18.764
FIRST TIME SEEING IT.

00:03:18.764 --> 00:03:21.837
&gt;&gt; Simon: SO THIS IS THE SEA!

00:03:21.837 --> 00:03:22.839
&gt;&gt; Kittan: LISTEN UP, PEOPLE!

00:03:22.839 --> 00:03:23.841
ALL THE WATER THAT’S IN THE

00:03:23.841 --> 00:03:25.511
SEA IS SALTY!

00:03:25.511 --> 00:03:26.513
&gt;&gt; Gimmy: SALTY SEAWATER,

00:03:26.513 --> 00:03:27.481
SALTY PEE WATER, SALTY SEAWATER,

00:03:27.481 --> 00:03:27.882
SALTY PEE WATER!

00:03:27.882 --> 00:03:28.884
&gt;&gt; Zorthy: YEAH, WHAT OF IT?

00:03:28.884 --> 00:03:29.886
&gt;&gt; Kidd: IT’S JUST SOMETHING TO

00:03:29.886 --> 00:03:30.822
GO AROUND, RIGHT?

00:03:30.822 --> 00:03:31.590
&gt;&gt; Jorgun: GO AROUND!

00:03:31.590 --> 00:03:32.859
&gt;&gt; Balinbow: GO AROUND!

00:03:32.859 --> 00:03:37.769
[all shout]

00:03:37.769 --> 00:03:38.504
&gt;&gt; Yoko: WHAT’S WITH THE

00:03:38.504 --> 00:03:39.673
ABSURD OUTFITS?

00:03:39.673 --> 00:03:40.474
&gt;&gt; Kittan: NO, STOP LOOKING...

00:03:40.474 --> 00:03:41.342
&gt;&gt; Kiyoh: IF YOU’VE COME TO THE

00:03:41.342 --> 00:03:42.411
SEA, YOU’VE GOTTA GO SWIMMING.

00:03:42.411 --> 00:03:42.912
YOU GOT NO CHOICE.

00:03:42.912 --> 00:03:44.448
&gt;&gt; Kinon: AS WELL AS SWIMMING,

00:03:44.448 --> 00:03:45.785
WE’LL BE ABLE TO CONFIRM IF THE

00:03:45.785 --> 00:03:46.419
WATER IS SALTY.

00:03:46.419 --> 00:03:47.354
&gt;&gt; Kiyal: THAT’S RIGHT.

00:03:47.354 --> 00:03:47.989
GET INTO YOUR SWIMSUITS, AND

00:03:47.989 --> 00:03:48.958
LET’S GO SWIMMING!

00:03:48.958 --> 00:03:50.494
&gt;&gt; Kidd: GO SWIMMING!

00:03:50.494 --> 00:03:51.630
&gt;&gt; Zorthy: IN OUR SWIMSUITS!

00:03:51.630 --> 00:03:52.899
&gt;&gt; Artenborough: AND THAT

00:03:52.899 --> 00:03:53.768
MEANS...

00:03:53.768 --> 00:03:56.640
[all shouting]

00:03:56.640 --> 00:03:59.913
&gt;&gt; Yoko: BUNCH OF CLOWNS!

00:03:59.913 --> 00:04:01.382
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

00:04:01.382 --> 00:04:01.984
STAY FOCUSED,

00:04:01.984 --> 00:04:02.919
YOU PERVERTED CREEPS.

00:04:02.919 --> 00:04:04.823
MAKING OUR WAY TO THE CAPITAL

00:04:04.823 --> 00:04:06.359
IS OUR TOP PRIORITY.

00:04:06.359 --> 00:04:07.428
WE DON’T HAVE TIME TO BE

00:04:07.428 --> 00:04:07.829
GOOFING OFF!

00:04:07.829 --> 00:04:08.864
&gt;&gt; Ron: ACTUALLY, THAT’S NOT

00:04:08.864 --> 00:04:10.467
ENTIRELY TRUE.

00:04:10.467 --> 00:04:10.835
&gt;&gt; Yoko: HUH?

00:04:10.835 --> 00:04:11.804
&gt;&gt; Ron: TAKE A LOOK.

00:04:11.804 --> 00:04:12.906
[beeping]

00:04:12.906 --> 00:04:13.841
THIS IS TEPPELIN PALACE

00:04:13.841 --> 00:04:15.310
AT THE HEART OF THE CAPITAL.

00:04:15.310 --> 00:04:16.713
&gt;&gt; Rossiu: OH, I SEE.

00:04:16.713 --> 00:04:17.949
SO IN ORDER FOR US TO

00:04:17.949 --> 00:04:18.884
SUCCESSFULLY MAKE OUR WAY

00:04:18.884 --> 00:04:19.820
TO TEPPELIN, WE HAVE NO

00:04:19.820 --> 00:04:20.922
CHOICE BUT TO CROSS THIS WATER.

00:04:20.922 --> 00:04:21.623
IS THAT RIGHT?

00:04:21.623 --> 00:04:22.559
&gt;&gt; Ron: RIGHT.

00:04:22.559 --> 00:04:23.727
BUT UNFORTUNATELY

00:04:23.727 --> 00:04:24.796
DAI‐GURREN IS LAND‐BASED,

00:04:24.796 --> 00:04:25.765
SO IT ISN’T WATERTIGHT.

00:04:25.765 --> 00:04:26.600
&gt;&gt; Simon: WELL THEN, HOW DO WE

00:04:26.600 --> 00:04:27.000
CROSS?

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:28.303
&gt;&gt; Ron: I HAD A FEELING

00:04:28.303 --> 00:04:28.838
SOMETHING LIKE THIS WOULD

00:04:28.838 --> 00:04:29.773
HAPPEN.

00:04:29.773 --> 00:04:31.543
SO FOR JUST SUCH AN OCCASION,

00:04:31.543 --> 00:04:32.679
I WHIPPED UP SOME AQUATIC GEAR!

00:04:32.679 --> 00:04:33.747
ALTHOUGH IT’S NOT QUITE

00:04:33.747 --> 00:04:34.916
READY YET, IT’LL STILL BE A

00:04:34.916 --> 00:04:36.018
LITTLE WHILE.

00:04:36.018 --> 00:04:37.354
&gt;&gt; girls: SO THAT MEANS...

00:04:37.354 --> 00:04:38.624
&gt;&gt; Ron: YES, LADIES, IT MEANS

00:04:38.624 --> 00:04:39.559
THAT YOU HAVE OODLES OF TIME TO

00:04:39.559 --> 00:04:40.561
GOOF OFF.

00:04:40.561 --> 00:04:42.599
&gt;&gt; girls: AWESOME!

00:04:42.599 --> 00:04:43.567
[laughing]

00:04:43.567 --> 00:04:45.036
&gt;&gt; all: AWESOME!

00:04:45.036 --> 00:04:49.646
[all shouting]

00:04:49.646 --> 00:04:50.815
&gt;&gt; Zorthy: HEY, COME ON!

00:04:50.815 --> 00:04:51.650
WHAT ARE WE WAITING FOR?

00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:53.821
LET’S SUIT UP!

00:04:53.821 --> 00:04:55.323
[all shouting]

00:04:55.323 --> 00:04:56.927
&gt;&gt; Ron: YOU’RE NOT GOING IN?

00:04:56.927 --> 00:04:58.029
&gt;&gt; Yoko: SWIMMING AROUND IN THE

00:04:58.029 --> 00:04:59.398
SEA UNDER THE SUN.

00:04:59.398 --> 00:05:01.002
I MEAN, I GUESS THAT

00:05:01.002 --> 00:05:02.672
MIGHT BE KINDA FUN.

00:05:02.672 --> 00:05:05.845
[gasping and giggling]

00:05:05.845 --> 00:05:07.849
&gt;&gt; Gimmy: HMM?

00:05:07.849 --> 00:05:09.385
BLAH! SALTY!

00:05:09.385 --> 00:05:09.920
[spitting]

00:05:09.920 --> 00:05:12.457
&gt;&gt; Ron: VERY SALTY.

00:05:12.457 --> 00:05:13.293
THIS IS WHERE ALL THE TEARS

00:05:13.293 --> 00:05:14.529
THAT STREAM DOWN THE FACES OF

00:05:14.529 --> 00:05:15.965
WOMEN END UP.

00:05:15.965 --> 00:05:18.303
&gt;&gt; [shouting]

00:05:18.303 --> 00:05:22.512
&gt;&gt; Zorthy: THEY’RE COMING!

00:05:22.512 --> 00:05:23.914
[all gasp]

00:05:27.555 --> 00:05:28.958
&gt;&gt; Zorthy: WHAT THE HELL?

00:05:28.958 --> 00:05:29.860
WHAT’S WITH THAT THING WRAPPED

00:05:29.860 --> 00:05:30.728
AROUND HER WAIST?

00:05:30.728 --> 00:05:31.730
&gt;&gt; Kidd: YEAH, WHAT’S UP WITH

00:05:31.730 --> 00:05:32.331
THAT?

00:05:32.331 --> 00:05:33.667
IT’S WEIRD.

00:05:33.667 --> 00:05:34.536
SHE’S SHOWING LESS SKIN

00:05:34.536 --> 00:05:35.370
THAN USUAL!

00:05:35.370 --> 00:05:36.607
&gt;&gt; Kittan: TAKE AWAY THE SKIN,

00:05:36.607 --> 00:05:37.709
AND WHAT’S SHE GOT LEFT?

00:05:37.709 --> 00:05:39.345
JUST A BIG‐ASS RIFLE.

00:05:39.345 --> 00:05:41.082
&gt;&gt; Yoko: I KNOW THAT, OKAY?!

00:05:41.082 --> 00:05:42.050
BESIDES, ISN’T IT BETTER

00:05:42.050 --> 00:05:42.986
TO LEAVE A LITTLE TO THE

00:05:42.986 --> 00:05:44.656
IMAGINATION?

00:05:44.656 --> 00:05:46.359
&gt;&gt; Kittan: ARE YOU AN IDIOT?!

00:05:46.359 --> 00:05:47.629
THAT’S NOT HOW IT WORKS!

00:05:47.629 --> 00:05:48.597
EVERYONE KNOWS, THE MORE SKIN

00:05:48.597 --> 00:05:49.599
THE BETTER!

00:05:49.599 --> 00:05:50.801
&gt;&gt; Yoko: AH, SCREW ALL OF YOU!

00:05:50.801 --> 00:05:51.803
I’LL FILL YOU FULL OF LEAD!

